Cary Elizabeth Hollinshead, a daughter of Mary Berg Hollinshead and Dr. William H. Hollinshead III of Rehoboth, Mass., was married yesterday to Dr. Terence Rossignol Strick, a son of Dr. Martine Rossignol Strick and Joseph Strick of Paris. The Rev. Michael Coburn performed the ceremony at St. Martin's Episcopal Church in Providence, R.I.
The bride and the bridegroom graduated from Princeton, where they met the week of her graduation and his second reunion.

Mrs. Hollinshead-Strick, 26, was until last month a designer of instructional software at iProgress, a Paris software company. She is to begin studying in September for a Ph.D. in comparative literature at the University of Pennsylvania. Her father is Rhode Island's director of family health in Providence. Her mother is an associate professor of art history at the University of Rhode Island in Kingston.

Mr. Strick, 27, is to become a postdoctoral fellow in August at the Cold Spring Harbor Laboratories on Long Island, where he will study chromosome structure. He received a doctorate in biophysics from the Ecole Normale Superieure in Paris. His mother is a paleoclimatologist at the Centre National de la Recherche Scientifique, the French national research organization in Paris. His father is a director, producer and writer of films and plays.
